{"video_id": "TnkpjshcIVA", "title": "SB 1.17.31-32 | HH Stoka Krishna Swami | 12-03-2023 | Daily Evening Bhagavatam Discourse", "speaker": "HH Stoka Krishna Swami", "youtube_url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TnkpjshcIVA", "duration": 1005, "segments": [{"start": 0.0, "end": 7.8, "text": " Om Agyanati Mirandhasya Gyananjanishalakaya Chakshurunmeelitam Yena Tasmai Shri Gurave Namaha"}, {"start": 7.8, "end": 14.76, "text": " Namah Om Vishnupadaya Krishna Preshtaya Bhutale Shri Mate Bhaktivedanta Swamin Nithinamine"}, {"start": 14.76, "end": 22.18, "text": " Namaste Saraswate Deve Gauravani Pracharine Nirvishesha Shunyavadi Pashchatya Deshatarine"}, {"start": 22.18, "end": 30.18, "text": " Jaya Shri Krishna Chaitanya Prabhu Nithyananda Shri Advaita Gadadhara Shri Vasadi Gauravakta Vrinda"}, {"start": 30.18, "end": 37.68, "text": " Hare Krishna Hare Krishna Krishna Krishna Hare Hare Hare Rama Hare Rama Rama Rama Hare Hare"}, {"start": 37.68, "end": 44.28, "text": " Om Namo Bhagavate Vasudevaya Narayanam Namaskritya Naram Chai Vanarottamam"}, {"start": 44.28, "end": 48.72, "text": " Deveem Saraswateem Vyasam Tato Jayam Udi Rayet"}, {"start": 48.72, "end": 52.16, "text": " In this session,"}, {"start": 52.18, "end": 60.72, "text": " we will be discussing from two verses, 31st and 32nd verses of the 17th chapter of the"}, {"start": 60.72, "end": 71.64, "text": " first canto of Srimad Bhagavata. The 31st verse is as follows. Rajavacha, after the"}, {"start": 71.64, "end": 78.16, "text": " Kali Purusha surrendered to Parikshit Maharaj, when he is about to be killed, he surrendered."}, {"start": 78.16, "end": 81.46000000000001, "text": " And what did Parikshit say?"}, {"start": 82.18, "end": 89.18, "text": " He definitely pardoned Kali Purusha, did not kill him. But what did he say?"}, {"start": 89.18, "end": 99.18, "text": " Na te gudakesha yaso dharanam baddhanjalervai bhayam astikinchit"}, {"start": 99.18, "end": 109.18, "text": " na vartitavyam bhavata katanchana kshetremadiyetvam adarmabandhuhu"}, {"start": 109.18, "end": 111.18, "text": " This is Parikshit's reply."}, {"start": 112.18, "end": 116.18, "text": " To Kali Purusha, the action of Kali Purusha."}, {"start": 116.18, "end": 119.18, "text": " The translation of this 31st verse."}, {"start": 119.18, "end": 122.18, "text": " The king thus said, it's King Parikshit."}, {"start": 122.18, "end": 125.18, "text": " We have inherited the fame of Arjuna."}, {"start": 125.18, "end": 131.18, "text": " Therefore, since you have surrendered yourself with folded hands, you need not fear for your life."}, {"start": 131.18, "end": 138.18, "text": " But you cannot remain in my kingdom, for you are the friend of irreligion."}, {"start": 138.18, "end": 140.18, "text": " Adarmabandhu."}, {"start": 140.18, "end": 141.18, "text": " Hmm."}, {"start": 141.18, "end": 145.18, "text": " So, Shri La Prabhupada explains."}, {"start": 145.18, "end": 153.18, "text": " The personality of Kali, who is the friend of all kinds of irreligiosities, may be excused if he surrenders."}, {"start": 153.18, "end": 163.18, "text": " But in all circumstances, he cannot be allowed to live as a citizen in any part of a welfare state."}, {"start": 163.18, "end": 169.18, "text": " Those who are violators of the fundamental principles of religion."}, {"start": 169.18, "end": 176.18, "text": " Fundamental principles of religion are not based on whether somebody is Hindu or Christian or Muslim."}, {"start": 176.18, "end": 177.18, "text": " No."}, {"start": 177.18, "end": 179.18, "text": " It is independent of that."}, {"start": 179.18, "end": 188.18, "text": " To practice austerity, cleanliness, truthfulness and mercy is there in all religious systems."}, {"start": 188.18, "end": 190.18, "text": " Bonafide religious systems."}, {"start": 190.18, "end": 191.18, "text": " Hmm."}, {"start": 191.18, "end": 193.18, "text": " So, they have to follow that."}, {"start": 193.18, "end": 198.18, "text": " If they become irreligious by breaking these principles."}, {"start": 198.18, "end": 209.18, "text": " Then they will not be allowed to live as a proper citizen in the kingdom or in the welfare state."}, {"start": 209.18, "end": 214.18, "text": " Being ruled by a proper administrator."}, {"start": 214.18, "end": 216.18, "text": " Hmm."}, {"start": 216.18, "end": 226.18, "text": " So, the principle of excusing or rather sparing the life of a surrendered soul is there."}, {"start": 226.18, "end": 227.18, "text": " Hmm."}, {"start": 227.18, "end": 234.18, "text": " But he cannot be allowed to live and influence the innocent people in a wrong way."}, {"start": 234.18, "end": 236.18, "text": " Sushila Prabhupada explains further."}, {"start": 236.18, "end": 244.18, "text": " The Pandavas were entrusted representatives of the personality of God and Lord Krishna."}, {"start": 244.18, "end": 249.18, "text": " Who practically brought into being the battle of Kurukshetra."}, {"start": 249.18, "end": 252.18, "text": " It is Krishna who arranged the battle of Kurukshetra."}, {"start": 252.18, "end": 255.18, "text": " Because before the battle of Kurukshetra."}, {"start": 255.18, "end": 259.18, "text": " Krishna was engaged in killing so many demons."}, {"start": 259.18, "end": 261.18, "text": " But in spite of killing."}, {"start": 261.18, "end": 262.18, "text": " Krishna killing so many demons."}, {"start": 262.18, "end": 269.18, "text": " Krishna began killing right on the lap of his mother as a small ten day old infant."}, {"start": 269.18, "end": 272.18, "text": " Poorthana came to kill Krishna."}, {"start": 272.18, "end": 274.18, "text": " But Krishna delivered her."}, {"start": 274.18, "end": 277.18, "text": " And after that so many demons came."}, {"start": 277.18, "end": 278.18, "text": " Pakasura."}, {"start": 278.18, "end": 279.18, "text": " Denukasura."}, {"start": 279.18, "end": 281.18, "text": " Aghasura."}, {"start": 281.18, "end": 283.18, "text": " Trinavarta."}, {"start": 283.18, "end": 284.18, "text": " So many demons came."}, {"start": 284.18, "end": 285.18, "text": " Shakatasura."}, {"start": 285.18, "end": 286.18, "text": " So many demons."}, {"start": 286.18, "end": 288.18, "text": " Krishna killed, killed, killed."}, {"start": 288.18, "end": 290.18, "text": " Of course Krishna's killing is delivering them."}, {"start": 290.18, "end": 291.18, "text": " Liberating them."}, {"start": 291.18, "end": 292.18, "text": " Purifying them."}, {"start": 292.18, "end": 298.18, "text": " But still Krishna had to deal with these demons."}, {"start": 298.18, "end": 302.18, "text": " And Krishna went on killing, killing, killing."}, {"start": 302.18, "end": 306.18, "text": " But the number of demons were so many."}, {"start": 306.18, "end": 310.18, "text": " Those who escaped."}, {"start": 310.18, "end": 312.18, "text": " Krishna brought them all together."}, {"start": 312.18, "end": 314.18, "text": " On the battlefield of."}, {"start": 314.18, "end": 317.18, "text": " Kurukshetra."}, {"start": 317.18, "end": 319.18, "text": " And through this battle of Kurukshetra."}, {"start": 319.18, "end": 323.18, "text": " Krishna arranged for all these remaining demons to be killed."}, {"start": 323.18, "end": 326.18, "text": " To bring down the burden of the earth."}, {"start": 326.18, "end": 328.18, "text": " So he arranged."}, {"start": 328.18, "end": 330.18, "text": " And Pandavas."}, {"start": 330.18, "end": 335.18, "text": " Even though Yudhishthira said I am not interested in ruling a kingdom."}, {"start": 335.18, "end": 337.18, "text": " And enjoying royal power."}, {"start": 337.18, "end": 338.18, "text": " No."}, {"start": 338.18, "end": 340.18, "text": " Even though it was his rightful claim."}, {"start": 340.18, "end": 341.18, "text": " But he said."}, {"start": 341.18, "end": 343.18, "text": " If Duryodhana wants to rule."}, {"start": 343.18, "end": 345.18, "text": " Let him rule."}, {"start": 345.18, "end": 349.18, "text": " I don't want to unnecessarily fight."}, {"start": 349.18, "end": 354.18, "text": " And I be the cause of so much killing happening."}, {"start": 354.18, "end": 356.18, "text": " In the battle."}, {"start": 356.18, "end": 360.18, "text": " But Krishna wanted this battle."}, {"start": 360.18, "end": 361.18, "text": " Why?"}, {"start": 361.18, "end": 367.18, "text": " To clear away the earth of the burden of these demons."}, {"start": 367.18, "end": 369.18, "text": " So through the battle of Kurukshetra."}, {"start": 369.18, "end": 372.18, "text": " Krishna arranged the remaining demons to be killed."}, {"start": 372.18, "end": 377.18, "text": " By the agency of the Pandavas."}, {"start": 377.18, "end": 381.18, "text": " So Krishna did not have any personal interest."}, {"start": 381.18, "end": 383.18, "text": " Not that he wanted to rule."}, {"start": 383.18, "end": 384.18, "text": " Or he wanted to enjoy."}, {"start": 384.18, "end": 386.18, "text": " Nothing."}, {"start": 386.18, "end": 387.18, "text": " So Krishna."}, {"start": 387.18, "end": 388.18, "text": " What did Krishna want?"}, {"start": 388.18, "end": 390.18, "text": " Through the battle of Kurukshetra."}, {"start": 390.18, "end": 393.18, "text": " Krishna wanted an ideal king like Maharaj Yudhishthira."}, {"start": 393.18, "end": 395.18, "text": " And his descendants like Maharaj Pariksit."}, {"start": 395.18, "end": 397.18, "text": " To rule the world."}, {"start": 397.18, "end": 399.18, "text": " Krishna wanted that."}, {"start": 399.18, "end": 400.18, "text": " Krishna always wants that."}, {"start": 400.18, "end": 403.18, "text": " It is explained."}, {"start": 403.18, "end": 406.18, "text": " In the Bhagavad Gita by Srila Prabhupada."}, {"start": 406.18, "end": 408.18, "text": " Krishna first instructed the Bhagavad Gita to."}, {"start": 408.18, "end": 410.18, "text": " This sun god Vivaswan."}, {"start": 410.18, "end": 412.18, "text": " Why?"}, {"start": 412.18, "end": 414.18, "text": " Because Krishna wants."}, {"start": 414.18, "end": 416.18, "text": " The rulers to rule."}, {"start": 416.18, "end": 418.18, "text": " Over the citizens."}, {"start": 418.18, "end": 420.18, "text": " According to the principles of Bhagavad Gita."}, {"start": 420.18, "end": 426.18, "text": " So the first duty of a ruler."}, {"start": 426.18, "end": 429.18, "text": " Is to protect the citizens."}, {"start": 429.18, "end": 433.18, "text": " Against material bondage to lust."}, {"start": 433.18, "end": 435.18, "text": " By."}, {"start": 435.18, "end": 437.18, "text": " Preaching Krishna consciousness."}, {"start": 437.18, "end": 439.18, "text": " God consciousness."}, {"start": 439.18, "end": 441.18, "text": " Making them God conscious."}, {"start": 441.18, "end": 443.18, "text": " And thereby human life."}, {"start": 443.18, "end": 445.18, "text": " Becomes successful."}, {"start": 445.18, "end": 447.18, "text": " For everyone."}, {"start": 447.18, "end": 449.18, "text": " Everyone can live peacefully."}, {"start": 449.18, "end": 451.18, "text": " By following the religious principles."}, {"start": 451.18, "end": 453.18, "text": " God conscious principles."}, {"start": 453.18, "end": 455.18, "text": " And everyone is able to make spiritual progress."}, {"start": 455.18, "end": 457.18, "text": " To ultimately attain."}, {"start": 457.18, "end": 459.18, "text": " The."}, {"start": 459.18, "end": 461.18, "text": " Perfection of human life."}, {"start": 461.18, "end": 463.18, "text": " Simply by following the."}, {"start": 463.18, "end": 465.18, "text": " Principles of Bhagavad Gita."}, {"start": 465.18, "end": 467.18, "text": " So."}, {"start": 467.18, "end": 469.18, "text": " Because."}, {"start": 469.18, "end": 471.18, "text": " Pariksit."}, {"start": 471.18, "end": 473.18, "text": " Yudhishthira."}, {"start": 473.18, "end": 475.18, "text": " All of them."}, {"start": 475.18, "end": 477.18, "text": " Are representatives of Krishna."}, {"start": 477.18, "end": 479.18, "text": " They cannot allow."}, {"start": 479.18, "end": 481.18, "text": " The friend of irreligiosity."}, {"start": 481.18, "end": 483.18, "text": " To flourish."}, {"start": 483.18, "end": 485.18, "text": " In their kingdom."}, {"start": 485.18, "end": 486.18, "text": " At the cost of."}, {"start": 486.18, "end": 488.18, "text": " The good fame of the Pandavas."}, {"start": 488.18, "end": 490.18, "text": " Pandavas are well known."}, {"start": 490.18, "end": 492.18, "text": " As."}, {"start": 492.18, "end": 494.18, "text": " Ideal rulers."}, {"start": 494.18, "end": 496.18, "text": " Perfect followers of."}, {"start": 496.18, "end": 498.18, "text": " Dharma."}, {"start": 498.18, "end": 500.18, "text": " Pure devotees of Krishna."}, {"start": 500.18, "end": 502.18, "text": " And they ruled perfectly."}, {"start": 502.18, "end": 504.18, "text": " So their good fame."}, {"start": 504.18, "end": 506.18, "text": " Cannot be."}, {"start": 506.18, "end": 508.18, "text": " Spoiled."}, {"start": 508.18, "end": 510.18, "text": " By Pariksit allowing."}, {"start": 510.18, "end": 512.1800000000001, "text": " This Kali Purusha who surrendered."}, {"start": 512.1800000000001, "end": 514.1800000000001, "text": " To live in his kingdom."}, {"start": 514.1800000000001, "end": 516.1800000000001, "text": " And spread a religion."}, {"start": 516.1800000000001, "end": 518.1800000000001, "text": " So Prabhupada says."}, {"start": 518.1800000000001, "end": 520.1800000000001, "text": " That is the way of wiping out corruption."}, {"start": 520.1800000000001, "end": 522.1800000000001, "text": " In the state."}, {"start": 524.1800000000001, "end": 526.1800000000001, "text": " The friends of irreligiosity."}, {"start": 526.1800000000001, "end": 528.1800000000001, "text": " Should be banished from the state."}, {"start": 528.1800000000001, "end": 530.1800000000001, "text": " And that will save the state from corruption."}, {"start": 532.1800000000001, "end": 534.1800000000001, "text": " The bad influence."}, {"start": 534.1800000000001, "end": 536.1800000000001, "text": " There are so many innocent people."}, {"start": 536.1800000000001, "end": 538.1800000000001, "text": " In this world."}, {"start": 538.1800000000001, "end": 540.1800000000001, "text": " It's like Prabhupada says."}, {"start": 540.1800000000001, "end": 542.1800000000001, "text": " By birth."}, {"start": 542.1800000000001, "end": 544.1800000000001, "text": " Does somebody have."}, {"start": 544.1800000000001, "end": 546.1800000000001, "text": " A cigarette in his mouth by birth."}, {"start": 546.1800000000001, "end": 548.1800000000001, "text": " Where did he."}, {"start": 548.1800000000001, "end": 550.1800000000001, "text": " Get this habit of smoking."}, {"start": 550.1800000000001, "end": 552.1800000000001, "text": " By bad influence."}, {"start": 552.1800000000001, "end": 554.1800000000001, "text": " Of other people."}, {"start": 554.1800000000001, "end": 556.1800000000001, "text": " Who are smoking."}, {"start": 556.1800000000001, "end": 558.1800000000001, "text": " It's only by bad influence."}, {"start": 558.1800000000001, "end": 560.1800000000001, "text": " Similarly."}, {"start": 562.1800000000001, "end": 564.1800000000001, "text": " The wrong influence."}, {"start": 564.1800000000001, "end": 566.1800000000001, "text": " Actually."}, {"start": 566.1800000000001, "end": 568.1800000000001, "text": " It victimizes innocent people."}, {"start": 570.1800000000001, "end": 572.1800000000001, "text": " To fall prey to bad habits."}, {"start": 572.1800000000001, "end": 574.1800000000001, "text": " And once they become."}, {"start": 574.1800000000001, "end": 576.1800000000001, "text": " Habituated to some."}, {"start": 576.1800000000001, "end": 578.1800000000001, "text": " It is very difficult."}, {"start": 578.1800000000001, "end": 580.1800000000001, "text": " For them to give up later on."}, {"start": 580.1800000000001, "end": 582.1800000000001, "text": " Even if they want to."}, {"start": 582.1800000000001, "end": 584.1800000000001, "text": " Except by Krishna Consciousness."}, {"start": 584.1800000000001, "end": 586.1800000000001, "text": " They cannot give up."}, {"start": 586.1800000000001, "end": 588.1800000000001, "text": " 32nd verse."}, {"start": 588.1800000000001, "end": 590.1800000000001, "text": " Tvam."}, {"start": 590.1800000000001, "end": 592.1800000000001, "text": " Vartamanam."}, {"start": 592.1800000000001, "end": 594.1800000000001, "text": " Naradeva Deheshu."}, {"start": 594.1800000000001, "end": 596.1800000000001, "text": " Anupravrttoyam."}, {"start": 596.1800000000001, "end": 598.1800000000001, "text": " Adharma Pugaha."}, {"start": 598.1800000000001, "end": 600.1800000000001, "text": " Lobho."}, {"start": 600.1800000000001, "end": 602.1800000000001, "text": " Anrutam."}, {"start": 602.1800000000001, "end": 604.1800000000001, "text": " Chauriyam."}, {"start": 604.1800000000001, "end": 606.1800000000001, "text": " Anaryam."}, {"start": 606.1800000000001, "end": 608.1800000000001, "text": " Jestha."}, {"start": 608.1800000000001, "end": 610.1800000000001, "text": " Chamaya."}, {"start": 610.1800000000001, "end": 612.1800000000001, "text": " Kalahascha."}, {"start": 612.1800000000001, "end": 614.1800000000001, "text": " Dambhaha."}, {"start": 614.1800000000001, "end": 616.1800000000001, "text": " The meaning of this 32nd verse."}, {"start": 616.1800000000001, "end": 618.1800000000001, "text": " Is."}, {"start": 618.1800000000001, "end": 620.1800000000001, "text": " If the personality of Kali."}, {"start": 620.1800000000001, "end": 622.1800000000001, "text": " Irreligion."}, {"start": 622.1800000000001, "end": 624.1800000000001, "text": " Is allowed to act as a man god."}, {"start": 624.1800000000001, "end": 626.1800000000001, "text": " Or an executive head."}, {"start": 626.1800000000001, "end": 628.1800000000001, "text": " Certainly irreligious principles."}, {"start": 628.1800000000001, "end": 630.1800000000001, "text": " Like greed."}, {"start": 630.1800000000001, "end": 632.1800000000001, "text": " Falsehood."}, {"start": 632.1800000000001, "end": 634.1800000000001, "text": " Robbery."}, {"start": 634.1800000000001, "end": 636.1800000000001, "text": " Incivility."}, {"start": 636.1800000000001, "end": 638.1800000000001, "text": " Deceit."}, {"start": 638.1800000000001, "end": 640.1800000000001, "text": " Okay."}, {"start": 640.1800000000001, "end": 642.1800000000001, "text": " Kali Purusha surrendered."}, {"start": 642.1800000000001, "end": 644.1800000000001, "text": " So his life was spared."}, {"start": 644.1800000000001, "end": 646.1800000000001, "text": " But he cannot be allowed to live."}, {"start": 646.1800000000001, "end": 648.1800000000001, "text": " Why?"}, {"start": 648.1800000000001, "end": 650.1800000000001, "text": " If he lives."}, {"start": 650.1800000000001, "end": 652.1800000000001, "text": " All these bad qualities will spread."}, {"start": 652.1800000000001, "end": 654.1800000000001, "text": " Among the people."}, {"start": 654.1800000000001, "end": 656.1800000000001, "text": " In the kingdom of Pariksit."}, {"start": 656.1800000000001, "end": 658.1800000000001, "text": " Greed."}, {"start": 658.1800000000001, "end": 660.1800000000001, "text": " Falsehood."}, {"start": 660.1800000000001, "end": 662.1800000000001, "text": " Robbery."}, {"start": 662.1800000000001, "end": 664.1800000000001, "text": " Treachery."}, {"start": 664.1800000000001, "end": 666.1800000000001, "text": " Misfortune."}, {"start": 666.1800000000001, "end": 668.1800000000001, "text": " That I am great."}, {"start": 668.1800000000001, "end": 670.1800000000001, "text": " Without actually having."}, {"start": 670.1800000000001, "end": 672.1800000000001, "text": " The real qualities."}, {"start": 672.1800000000001, "end": 674.1800000000001, "text": " So in the purport."}, {"start": 674.1800000000001, "end": 676.1800000000001, "text": " Srila Prabhupada says."}, {"start": 676.1800000000001, "end": 678.1800000000001, "text": " The principles of religion."}, {"start": 678.1800000000001, "end": 680.1800000000001, "text": " Namely austerity."}, {"start": 680.1800000000001, "end": 682.1800000000001, "text": " Cleanliness."}, {"start": 682.1800000000001, "end": 684.1800000000001, "text": " Mercy and truthfulness."}, {"start": 684.1800000000001, "end": 686.1800000000001, "text": " As we have already discussed."}, {"start": 686.1800000000001, "end": 688.1800000000001, "text": " May be followed by."}, {"start": 688.1800000000001, "end": 690.1800000000001, "text": " The follower of any faith."}, {"start": 690.1800000000001, "end": 692.1800000000001, "text": " As regard religious principles."}, {"start": 692.1800000000001, "end": 694.1800000000001, "text": " Nobody can say."}, {"start": 694.1800000000001, "end": 696.1800000000001, "text": " Hindus."}, {"start": 696.1800000000001, "end": 698.1800000000001, "text": " No."}, {"start": 698.1800000000001, "end": 700.1800000000001, "text": " There is no such thing as."}, {"start": 700.1800000000001, "end": 702.1800000000001, "text": " Bhagavatam is meant for Hindus."}, {"start": 704.1800000000001, "end": 706.1800000000001, "text": " These four principles."}, {"start": 706.1800000000001, "end": 708.1800000000001, "text": " Are the fundamental principles."}, {"start": 708.1800000000001, "end": 710.1800000000001, "text": " Of."}, {"start": 710.1800000000001, "end": 712.1800000000001, "text": " God consciousness."}, {"start": 712.1800000000001, "end": 714.1800000000001, "text": " No matter."}, {"start": 714.1800000000001, "end": 716.1800000000001, "text": " Which religious system somebody may follow."}, {"start": 716.1800000000001, "end": 718.1800000000001, "text": " Which bona fide religious system they may follow."}, {"start": 718.1800000000001, "end": 720.1800000000001, "text": " The same."}, {"start": 720.1800000000001, "end": 722.1800000000001, "text": " Principles are given in all scriptures."}, {"start": 722.1800000000001, "end": 724.1800000000001, "text": " So Prabhupada says."}, {"start": 724.1800000000001, "end": 726.1800000000001, "text": " There is no need to turn."}, {"start": 726.1800000000001, "end": 728.1800000000001, "text": " From Hindu to Mohammedan."}, {"start": 728.1800000000001, "end": 730.1800000000001, "text": " To Christian or some other faith."}, {"start": 730.1800000000001, "end": 732.1800000000001, "text": " And thus become a renegade."}, {"start": 732.1800000000001, "end": 734.1800000000001, "text": " And not follow the principles of religion."}, {"start": 734.1800000000001, "end": 736.1800000000001, "text": " Renegade means."}, {"start": 736.1800000000001, "end": 738.1800000000001, "text": " A separatist."}, {"start": 738.1800000000001, "end": 740.1800000000001, "text": " Or a rebel."}, {"start": 740.1800000000001, "end": 742.1800000000001, "text": " No need."}, {"start": 742.1800000000001, "end": 744.1800000000001, "text": " So."}, {"start": 744.1800000000001, "end": 746.1800000000001, "text": " It is not that."}, {"start": 746.1800000000001, "end": 748.1800000000001, "text": " People."}, {"start": 748.1800000000001, "end": 750.1800000000001, "text": " In the name of."}, {"start": 750.1800000000001, "end": 752.1800000000001, "text": " I don't believe."}, {"start": 752.1800000000001, "end": 754.1800000000001, "text": " Or don't accept."}, {"start": 754.1800000000001, "end": 756.1800000000001, "text": " Some particular religious system."}, {"start": 756.1800000000001, "end": 758.1800000000001, "text": " No."}, {"start": 758.1800000000001, "end": 760.1800000000001, "text": " You cannot live."}, {"start": 760.1800000000001, "end": 762.1800000000001, "text": " In a civilized society."}, {"start": 762.1800000000001, "end": 764.1800000000001, "text": " And spread irreligion."}, {"start": 764.1800000000001, "end": 766.1800000000001, "text": " Among the innocent people."}, {"start": 766.1800000000001, "end": 768.1800000000001, "text": " And thereby corrupt."}, {"start": 768.1800000000001, "end": 770.1800000000001, "text": " The atmosphere."}, {"start": 770.1800000000001, "end": 772.1800000000001, "text": " Pure atmosphere."}, {"start": 772.1800000000001, "end": 774.1800000000001, "text": " Of the state."}, {"start": 774.1800000000001, "end": 776.1800000000001, "text": " The Bhagavatam religion urges."}, {"start": 776.1800000000001, "end": 778.1800000000001, "text": " Following the principles of religion."}, {"start": 778.1800000000001, "end": 780.1800000000001, "text": " Bhagavata Dharma."}, {"start": 780.1800000000001, "end": 782.1800000000001, "text": " Is the dominant."}, {"start": 782.1800000000001, "end": 784.1800000000001, "text": " Of people's belief system."}, {"start": 784.1800000000001, "end": 786.1800000000001, "text": " This is the important point."}, {"start": 786.1800000000001, "end": 788.1800000000001, "text": " Like Srila Prabhupada."}, {"start": 788.1800000000001, "end": 790.1800000000001, "text": " Traveled all over the world."}, {"start": 790.1800000000001, "end": 792.1800000000001, "text": " And preached the Bhagavata Dharma."}, {"start": 792.1800000000001, "end": 794.1800000000001, "text": " Of simply chanting the names of God."}, {"start": 794.1800000000001, "end": 796.1800000000001, "text": " Srila Prabhupada said."}, {"start": 796.1800000000001, "end": 798.1800000000001, "text": " If you have objection to chanting name of Krishna."}, {"start": 798.1800000000001, "end": 800.1800000000001, "text": " You may chant the name of God."}, {"start": 800.1800000000001, "end": 802.1800000000001, "text": " As revealed in your."}, {"start": 802.1800000000001, "end": 804.1800000000001, "text": " Bonafide religious system."}, {"start": 804.1800000000001, "end": 806.1800000000001, "text": " But chanting the name of God."}, {"start": 806.1800000000001, "end": 808.1800000000001, "text": " Is the principle."}, {"start": 808.1800000000001, "end": 810.1800000000001, "text": " Of Bhagavata Dharma."}, {"start": 810.1800000000001, "end": 812.1800000000001, "text": " So you chant."}, {"start": 814.1800000000001, "end": 816.1800000000001, "text": " When Prabhupada pointed out."}, {"start": 816.1800000000001, "end": 818.1800000000001, "text": " That."}, {"start": 818.1800000000001, "end": 820.1800000000001, "text": " In the."}, {"start": 820.1800000000001, "end": 822.1800000000001, "text": " Islam religion."}, {"start": 822.1800000000001, "end": 824.1800000000001, "text": " They say."}, {"start": 824.1800000000001, "end": 826.1800000000001, "text": " Allah is the name of God."}, {"start": 826.1800000000001, "end": 828.1800000000001, "text": " As revealed in their scripture."}, {"start": 828.1800000000001, "end": 830.1800000000001, "text": " So he is supreme."}, {"start": 830.1800000000001, "end": 832.1800000000001, "text": " And they glorify him."}, {"start": 832.1800000000001, "end": 834.1800000000001, "text": " In so many ways."}, {"start": 834.1800000000001, "end": 836.1800000000001, "text": " In the Quran."}, {"start": 836.1800000000001, "end": 838.1800000000001, "text": " In the Bible."}, {"start": 838.1800000000001, "end": 840.1800000000001, "text": " Father in heaven."}, {"start": 840.1800000000001, "end": 842.1800000000001, "text": " The name."}, {"start": 842.1800000000001, "end": 844.1800000000001, "text": " The name of the supreme Lord."}, {"start": 844.1800000000001, "end": 846.1800000000001, "text": " Is glorified in the Bible."}, {"start": 846.1800000000001, "end": 848.1800000000001, "text": " So God is one."}, {"start": 850.1800000000001, "end": 852.1800000000001, "text": " Though different names."}, {"start": 852.1800000000001, "end": 854.1800000000001, "text": " He may be referred to."}, {"start": 854.1800000000001, "end": 856.1800000000001, "text": " In different bonafide religious systems."}, {"start": 856.1800000000001, "end": 858.1800000000001, "text": " But God is one."}, {"start": 858.1800000000001, "end": 860.1800000000001, "text": " Supreme means."}, {"start": 860.1800000000001, "end": 862.1800000000001, "text": " Only one person."}, {"start": 862.1800000000001, "end": 864.1800000000001, "text": " Nobody is equal to him."}, {"start": 864.1800000000001, "end": 866.1800000000001, "text": " Nobody is above him."}, {"start": 866.1800000000001, "end": 868.1800000000001, "text": " So that principle."}, {"start": 868.1800000000001, "end": 870.1800000000001, "text": " He is explaining."}, {"start": 870.1800000000001, "end": 872.1800000000001, "text": " Sticking to dogmas and formulas."}, {"start": 872.1800000000001, "end": 874.1800000000001, "text": " Without attaining the real principles."}, {"start": 874.1800000000001, "end": 876.1800000000001, "text": " Is not good."}, {"start": 876.1800000000001, "end": 878.1800000000001, "text": " A secular state may be impartial."}, {"start": 878.1800000000001, "end": 880.1800000000001, "text": " To any type of faith."}, {"start": 880.1800000000001, "end": 882.1800000000001, "text": " But the state cannot be indifferent."}, {"start": 882.1800000000001, "end": 884.1800000000001, "text": " To the principles of religion."}, {"start": 884.1800000000001, "end": 886.1800000000001, "text": " As above mentioned."}, {"start": 886.1800000000001, "end": 888.1800000000001, "text": " Secular state means."}, {"start": 888.1800000000001, "end": 890.1800000000001, "text": " The state will allow people to follow."}, {"start": 890.1800000000001, "end": 892.1800000000001, "text": " Either Christianity or Islam."}, {"start": 892.1800000000001, "end": 894.1800000000001, "text": " Or whatever."}, {"start": 894.1800000000001, "end": 896.1800000000001, "text": " But they cannot break the fundamental principles."}, {"start": 896.1800000000001, "end": 898.1800000000001, "text": " Like austerity."}, {"start": 898.1800000000001, "end": 900.1800000000001, "text": " Cleanliness."}, {"start": 900.1800000000001, "end": 902.1800000000001, "text": " Mercy."}, {"start": 902.1800000000001, "end": 904.1800000000001, "text": " Truthfulness."}, {"start": 904.1800000000001, "end": 906.1800000000001, "text": " They cannot break that."}, {"start": 906.1800000000001, "end": 908.1800000000001, "text": " They are punishable."}, {"start": 908.1800000000001, "end": 910.1800000000001, "text": " If they break these principles."}, {"start": 910.1800000000001, "end": 912.1800000000001, "text": " Irrespective of what their belief system is."}, {"start": 912.1800000000001, "end": 914.1800000000001, "text": " In the age of Kali."}, {"start": 914.1800000000001, "end": 916.1800000000001, "text": " The executive heads of state."}, {"start": 916.1800000000001, "end": 918.1800000000001, "text": " Will be indifferent to such religious principles."}, {"start": 918.1800000000001, "end": 920.1800000000001, "text": " And therefore."}, {"start": 920.1800000000001, "end": 922.1800000000001, "text": " Under their patronage."}, {"start": 922.1800000000001, "end": 924.1800000000001, "text": " The opponents of religious principles."}, {"start": 924.1800000000001, "end": 926.1800000000001, "text": " Will follow."}, {"start": 926.1800000000001, "end": 928.1800000000001, "text": " And so there will be no meaning to propaganda."}, {"start": 928.1800000000001, "end": 930.1800000000001, "text": " Crying."}, {"start": 930.1800000000001, "end": 932.1800000000001, "text": " To stop corruption in the state."}, {"start": 932.1800000000001, "end": 934.1800000000001, "text": " People want."}, {"start": 934.1800000000001, "end": 936.1800000000001, "text": " To root out corruption."}, {"start": 936.1800000000001, "end": 938.1800000000001, "text": " And they are harassed by this corruption."}, {"start": 938.1800000000001, "end": 940.1800000000001, "text": " But the corruption is the natural."}, {"start": 940.1800000000001, "end": 942.1800000000001, "text": " Consequence."}, {"start": 942.1800000000001, "end": 944.1800000000001, "text": " Of people breaking."}, {"start": 944.1800000000001, "end": 946.1800000000001, "text": " The fundamental religious principles."}, {"start": 946.1800000000001, "end": 948.1800000000001, "text": " You see."}, {"start": 948.1800000000001, "end": 950.1800000000001, "text": " There is a connection."}, {"start": 950.1800000000001, "end": 952.1800000000001, "text": " If people don't practice austerity."}, {"start": 952.1800000000001, "end": 954.1800000000001, "text": " Somebody may think."}, {"start": 954.1800000000001, "end": 956.1800000000001, "text": " Oh he doesn't believe in."}, {"start": 956.1800000000001, "end": 958.1800000000001, "text": " Doing tapasya."}, {"start": 958.1800000000001, "end": 960.1800000000001, "text": " The form of fasting."}, {"start": 960.1800000000001, "end": 962.1800000000001, "text": " So it's okay."}, {"start": 962.1800000000001, "end": 964.1800000000001, "text": " Let him not follow."}, {"start": 964.1800000000001, "end": 966.1800000000001, "text": " No."}, {"start": 966.1800000000001, "end": 968.1800000000001, "text": " That will result in the person becoming."}, {"start": 968.1800000000001, "end": 970.1800000000001, "text": " Afflicted."}, {"start": 970.1800000000001, "end": 972.1800000000001, "text": " By greed."}, {"start": 972.1800000000001, "end": 974.1800000000001, "text": " By falsehood."}, {"start": 974.1800000000001, "end": 976.1800000000001, "text": " By cheating."}, {"start": 976.1800000000001, "end": 978.1800000000001, "text": " So many bad qualities."}, {"start": 978.1800000000001, "end": 980.1800000000001, "text": " The person will develop."}, {"start": 980.1800000000001, "end": 982.1800000000001, "text": " So therefore."}, {"start": 982.1800000000001, "end": 984.1800000000001, "text": " To protect people."}, {"start": 984.1800000000001, "end": 986.1800000000001, "text": " The enforcement."}, {"start": 986.1800000000001, "end": 988.1800000000001, "text": " The law enforcing authority."}, {"start": 988.1800000000001, "end": 990.1800000000001, "text": " Should enforce."}, {"start": 990.1800000000001, "end": 992.1800000000001, "text": " That everyone should follow."}, {"start": 992.1800000000001, "end": 994.1800000000001, "text": " Irrespective of their religious affiliation."}, {"start": 994.1800000000001, "end": 996.1800000000001, "text": " The four fundamental pillars of dharma."}, {"start": 996.1800000000001, "end": 998.1800000000001, "text": " Austerity."}, {"start": 998.1800000000001, "end": 1000.1800000000001, "text": " Cleanliness."}, {"start": 1000.1800000000001, "end": 1002.1800000000001, "text": " Mercy."}, {"start": 1002.1800000000001, "end": 1004.1800000000001, "text": " And truthfulness."}, {"start": 1004.1800000000001, "end": 1006.1800000000001, "text": " I will stop here."}, {"start": 1006.1800000000001, "end": 1008.1800000000001, "text": " Thank you very much."}, {"start": 1008.1800000000001, "end": 1010.1800000000001, "text": " Hare Krishna."}]}